Kieni MP Kanini Kega has told off independent candidates and urged them to stop giving ultimatums to President Uhuru Kenyatta over the General Election.He said the candidates are dangerous and urged them to accept defeat and work with Jubilee nominees.Kega (pictured) spoke at Kanyagia in his constituency on Monday, where he disbursed CDF bursary funds to children. The MP accused businesspeople of colluding with NASA to politicise the issue on the rising cost of maize. The MP also invited the opposition to the Madaraka Day celebrations in Nyeri, calling for tolerance across the country. He called on the NASA team to concede that they are afraid they will lose the election. Kega urged voters to verify their names on the IEBC register now instead of waiting for the last-minute rush.